  "original_title": "\u2019\u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bc1\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'Government failed to deliver on promises'",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former President Maithripala Sirisena has said that the government that came to ensure national security has now failed to fulfill that promise.",
        "He said this while participating in a press conference held yesterday (1) in Colombo.",
        "The main idea of \u200b\u200bstrengthening national security was mentioned in the Motu party's election campaign.",
        "However, people know what has happened to national security in the last 3 years.",
        "In this situation, what has happened to the national security that the leaders said during the 2019 election campaign and is there national security in the country now? Former President Maithripala Sirisena has also questioned the government. (a)"
      ],
